<FIRST>r i PM-East-West-Accord     01-13 0233</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-East-West-Accord,0244</SECOND>
<HEAD>Key Provisions of Accord</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Also in Saturday AMs report.</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-East-West, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VIENNA, Austria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Key provisions of the human rights accord
tentatively approved Friday by 35 nations at the Helsinki review
conference:
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   _ To give prisoners humane treatment, and stop the abuse of
psychiatry against political prisoners;
   _ To decide outstanding emigration applications within six
months, applications for East bloc citizens to join Western spouses
within three months, for family reunions within one month, and for
urgent medical travel or funeral attendance within three days;
   _ To allow religious education, the dissemination of religious
literature and church charity;
   _ To encourage tourism, particularly by allowing Western tourists
to stay in East bloc homes;
   _ To allow freer spread of information, halting East bloc jamming
of Western radio stations;
   _ To stop expelling journalists or taking other measures against
them over the content of their reports;
   _ To allow independent groups to monitor their governments' human
rights behavior and action on the environment;
   _ To exchange much more economic data to facilitate Western
business with the East;
   _ To publish widely the text of the Helsinki Final Act, the
Vienna document and conditions for emigration or travel abroad; and
   _ To hold annual conferences on human rights, and to allow any
Helsinki signatory to raise human rights affairs on a bilateral
level with any other signatory state.
</TEXT>
