<HEAD>11-Year-Old Burns School For Love, Officials Say</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An 11-year-old set fire to his
school in hopes of being transferred to the one his sweetheart
attends, the fire marshal says.
   Not only was the boy arrested, but the girl broke up with him
when she found out about the $1 million blaze, said City Fire
Marshal Jerry Catoe.
   The boy and two friends _ boys ages 12 and 7 _ were charged
Wednesday with arson and burglary in the nighttime fire Dec. 30 at
the Southboro Elementary School.
   ``The motive was love,'' the fire marshal said.
   The boys were suspended and may face expulsion, Superintendent
Tom Mills said. They were released into their parents' custody.
   The fire occurred over the Christmas break, and school opened as
scheduled afterward.
   The 11-year-old often had threatened to burn the school, and took
matches and a flammable liquid to start the fire, Catoe said.
   Catoe said the boy had offered to let his girlfriend help set the
fire so he could join the 12-year-old at South Olive Elmentary
School, but she refused.
