<HEAD>Hearse Driver Crushed To Death By Casket</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COLD SPRING, Ky. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The driver of a hearse was crushed to
death between the dashboard and a full casket in a head-on
collision, authorities said.
   Jack Volkering, 59, of Fort Wright, was returning from a funeral
Mass on Wednesday when a car driven by Lonnie Stephens, 23, of
Bellevue crossed the road and struck the hearse, Police Chief Gene
Schweitzer said Thursday.
   The casket broke through a metal holding post and struck
Volkering in the back as the dashboard and steering wheel hit him in
the chest, said Dr. Fred Stine, Campbell County coroner. Stine said
Volkering probably suffocated.
   Volkering was pronounced dead at St. Luke Hospital. Stephens was
not seriously hurt.
   Volkering was transporting a body to the livery service he worked
for.
   Another hearse picked up the body immediately after the accident
and it was buried Thursday as scheduled, said Bob Lucas of the
Alexandria Funeral Home.
