<SECOND>PM-Handsome Rapist,0298</SECOND>
<HEAD>Man Who Claimed Women Couldn't Resist Him Convicted Of Rape</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTA ANA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A businessman who said his good looks
and sexual magnetism made him irresistible to women has been
convicted of five sexual assaults, including three rapes.
   Thomas J. Panichas, 32, of Fountain Valley could receive up to 89
years in prison at sentencing March 3. He was found guilty on 19
felony counts for attacks on five women from 1985 to 1988.
   Panichas, who at one point in his testimony needed several
minutes and a pen and paper to calculate his dozens of romantic
conquests, insisted all five women consented and enjoyed his
advances.
   In some cases, he said, the women took off their clothes or
ripped out portions of their panty hose to entice him.
   ``I don't see how this is incredible,'' he testified. ``I guess
I'm a good-looking man in their eyes.''
   The women, all in their early 20s with long blond hair, testified
that after meeting Panichas at a nightclub or during a job interview
at his cellular phone business, he wined and dined them and boasted
of running a firm that would gross $190 million.
   They said that the 6-foot-5 Panichas then attacked them in his
office or in the front seat of his Cadillac. One woman said that
when she closed her eyes during an attack, Panichas forced them open
with his fingers.
   Investigators said that Panichas' company actually was in serious
financial trouble and that he had sold only a handful of phones.
   The jury deliberated about six hours.
   ``He was pretty grandiose about his claims of being so sexually
active,'' said jury foreman Kenneth Van Buskirk. ``It was pretty
easy to see through him.''
