<FIRST>r a AM-StAlbansBodies     01-13 0261</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-St Albans Bodies,0268</SECOND>
<HEAD>Third Body Found in St. Albans</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. ALBANS, W.Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police said Friday they have found the
battered body of the grandmother of a man charged with the shotgun
slayings of his two housemates last weekend.
   The search is continuing for two other people who lived with the
suspect, police said.
   Mark Southern McCallister, 19, of St. Albans, was charged Tuesday
with two counts of first-degree murder in the deaths of Otis Gerald
Sanson, 25, and his brother Billy Lee, 27, who lived with
McCallister in a mobile home.
   Otis Sanson's body was found in a trailer next to the mobile
home, while his brother's body was found in a cardboard crate nearby.
   Deputies found the body of McCallister's grandmother, Charlotte
Ruby Ferrell, 69, in the bedroom of her St. Albans home late
Thursday wrapped in curtains and sheets, said Kanawha County
Sheriff's Department Cpl. John Rutherford. No charges have been
filed, he said.
   ``We haven't had time to even think about that,'' Rutherford
said. ``We're treating it as an apparent homicide.''
   Mrs. Ferrell's body was found after relatives noticed that her
mail hadn't been picked up for several days, Rutherford said. He
said an autopsy will be performed.
   McCallister is being held in the Kanawha County Jail pending a
bond hearing next week, Rutherford said.
   Two other people who lived with McCallister have not been seen
since October, Rutherford said. Bonnie Sanson Pauley and her
boyfriend, Jimmy Price, were reported missing this fall and
authorities believe they may be living in Texas, he said.
</TEXT>
