<SECOND>AM-Census-Asians,110</SECOND>
<HEAD>1990 Census Form to Include Asian Checkoff</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Asians will be given a choice of nationalities
to check off on the 1990 census form, the Census Bureau announced
Friday.
   Bureau officials, politicians and members of the Asian community
have been debating whether to provide the checkoff on the forms or
simply to provide a blank space for Asians to specify their
nationality.
   The checkoff system was decided on at the request of the Asian
community, officials said. But an additional blank line will also be
included for people who do not fit into the suggested categories.
   Checkoff categories will be the same as those offered in 1980,
officials said. They were Japanese, Chinese, Filipino, Korean,
Vietnamese, Asian Indian, Hawaiian, Guamian and Samoan.
