<FIRST>r i AM-Germany-Crash-List     01-13 0359</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Germany-Crash-List,0378</SECOND>
<HEAD>Fatal Crashes of Military Aircraft</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Germany-Crash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BREMEN, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Crashes involving military aircraft
have killed 103 people in West Germany within the last year. Here is
a list:
</TEXT>
<NOTE>1988</NOTE>
<TEXT>
   MARCH 31 _ U.S. Air Force F-16 jet crashes in the town of Forst,
killing the pilot and a man on the ground.
   APRIL 5 _ Two-man crew aboard a U.S. Army helicopter is killed
when the aircraft crashes near Stuttgart.
   MAY 6 _ British Royal Air Force Chinook helicopter strikes a
loading ramp with its rotor blade at Hanover airport at an air show,
killing two crewmen.
   MAY 20 _ British Royal Air Force pilot is killed when his Harrier
jet crashes near Gutersloh.
   JUNE 9 _ U.S. Army UH1H helicopter crashes near Krumbach in
Bavaria, killing the three-man crew.
   JUNE 14 _ Co-pilot of a OH58 U.S. Army helicopter is killed when
it crashes in Starnberg lake near Munich.
   JUNE 15 _ Two-man West German crew of a Phantom jet fighter is
killed when it crashes near the town of Coesfeld.
   JUNE 29 _ U.S. Air Force pilot is killed when two F-16s collide
while flying near Mainz.
   JULY 3 _ Nine people aboard a West German military helicopter are
killed when it crashes in the Bavarian Alps.
   JULY 26 _ Pilot of an ultra-light private plane dies in a
collision with West German air force Tornado jet flying near Munich.
   AUG. 28 _ Three Italian air force stunt jets collide at an air
show at the U.S. Ramstein Air Base; one of the planes plows into the
watching crowd. Sixty-seven spectators and the three pilots are
killed.
   SEPT. 7 _ British Royal Air Force pilot is killed in a crash of a
Jaguar military jet near the town of Calw in the Black Forest region.
   DEC. 8 _ U.S. Air Force A-10 Thunderbolt crashes into a
residential neighborhood in the city of Remscheid, killing the pilot
and five people on the ground.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>1989</NOTE>
<TEXT>
   JAN. 13 _ British warplane strays into squadron of West German
jet fighters near the northern town of Wiesmor and collides with
two, killing two British fliers.
</TEXT>
