<FIRST>u a BC-SPE--Taxes:Deductions CLARIFICATION   01-13 0111</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-SPE--Taxes: Deductions, CLARIFICATION,0110</SECOND>
<BYLINE>CLARIFICATION</BYLINE>
<HEAD>Eds: Members that used story slugged ``Taxes and Your Money: Deductions,''
moved Jan. 9 as b1028, may wish to use the following.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Associated Press, in a report on deductions
that was part of a recent series of articles on the federal income
tax, said scientology fees are not deductible.
   The Internal Revenue Service considers scientology fees
non-deductible personal expenses, but appellate courts for the 2nd,
6th and 8th circuits have ruled the fees are deductible charitable
contributions. Those cases are under appeal, and if the Supreme
Court sides with the Church of Scientology, the IRS will have to
allow the deductions.
</TEXT>
