<SECOND>AM-Northwest-Lost Wheel, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0736,0180</SECOND>
<HEAD>Jet Lands Safely After Losing Wheel</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: New throughout; CORRECTS time of landing, adds other details;
no pickup.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROMULUS, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Northwest Airlines jetliner that lost a
wheel upon takeoff from Washington landed safely Friday at Detroit
Metropolitan Airport, officials said.
   Flight 345 landed without incident at 4:53 p.m. EST and taxied
under its own power to the passenger gate, said Mark Sparks of the
Wayne County Emergency Management Division.
   Northwest spokesman Bob Gibbons said the lost wheel was one of
four on the right main landing gear. The landing gear assembly has a
total of 10 wheels, he said, adding that the cause of the mishap had
not been determined.
   The Boeing 757, carrying 143 passengers and six crew members,
departed Washington National Airport at 2:09 p.m. EST when it lost
the wheel, which severely damaged a private plane on the ground at
Washington National Airport, authorities said.
   The aircraft remained at Metropolitan Airport for inspection
Friday night while Flight 345 continued to San Francisco using
another plane, Gibbons said.
</TEXT>
