<TEXT>
   A federal appeals court rejected defense
arguments to prevent a second trial in the stock-manipulation case
against GAF Corp. and a key company officer, two days after a
mistrial was declared.
   The ruling by the 2nd Circuit Court of Appeals after a brief
hearing means jury selection for a new trial will commence next
Tuesday in U.S. District Court, lawyers involved in the case said
Thursday.
