<TEXT>
   The British government temporarily barred General
Electric Co. PLC and Siemens AG from proceeding with their hostile,
$3.6 billion takeover bid for British defense contractor Plessey Co.
   Trade Secretary Lord Young said Thursday he referred the bid to
the Monopolies and Mergers Commission to determine its effects on
competition, particularly in defense electronics and air traffic
control equipment.
   Young asked the commission to make its recommendation within
three months.
</TEXT>
