<SECOND>BC-EEC-Unemployment,0078</SECOND>
<HEAD>EEC November Jobless Rate Dips</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The unemploymnent rate in the 12-nation
European Economic Community stood at a seasonally adjusted 10.1
percent in November, 0.1 percentage point lower than the previous
month, a report released Friday said.
   Eurostat, the EEC's statistical service, estimated that 15.44
million people were unemployed in the EEC at the end of November,
down from roughly 15.49 million in October and 15.65 million in
September.
</TEXT>
