<FIRST>u f AM-Britain-Natwest     01-13 0215</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Britain-Natwest,0224</SECOND>
<HEAD>Natwest Discontinues U.S. Primary Bond Dealership</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   National Westminster Bank PLC said its U.S.-based
County Natwest Government Securities Inc. would abandon its primary
bond dealership after operating in the U.S. Treasuries market in New
York for just over three months.
   Natwest said some of the 100 people employed by the dealership
might be transferred within the company.
   The decision to withdraw resulted from an assessment of the costs
involved in the primary dealership, Natwest said.
   ``Continued expansion of the business would require the injection
of substantial additional capital, but analysis of the prospective
long-term return on capital has persuaded us that further investment
cannot be justified in the context of our overall strategy,''
Natwest said in a statement.
   County Natwest Government Securities was named one of 46 primary
dealers in U.S. government securities on Sept. 29, the last time new
primary dealers were added to the list by the Federal Reserve Bank
of New York.
   In December, the Fed recommended that Natwest inject $50 million
to $100 million into the dealership to meet capitalization
requirements.
   Primary dealers are government bond dealers that do business
directly with the Federal Reserve Bank of New York. They are
required to make markets in all government issues and to participate
at all Treasury auctions.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
